sequenceDiagram
    participant TM as Task Manager
    participant AO as Agent Orchestrator
    participant AG as Specialized Agent
    participant KR as Knowledge Repository
    participant TIG as Tool Integration Gateway
    participant EE as Execution Engine
    participant GM as Governance Module

    TM->>TM: Marks task as ready (dependencies resolved)
    TM->>AO: Ready task available for assignment
    AO->>AO: Selects appropriate Specialized Agent for task type
    AO->>AG: Task assignment + context references
    AG->>KR: Read required artifacts (read-only)
    KR-->>AG: Foundational docs, specs, architecture views, UL

    AG->>TIG: Send inference request to AI Provider
    TIG-->>AG: AI model response

    opt MCP tools required
        AG->>TIG: Invoke MCP Server for extended capabilities
        TIG-->>AG: Tool results
    end

    AG->>EE: Deliver artifact candidate
    EE->>EE: Artifact Producer assembles production-ready artifact
    EE->>EE: Validation Engine checks acceptance criteria

    alt Validation fails
        EE->>AO: Rejection report
        AO->>TM: Update task state to Failed
        TM->>TM: May re-queue or mark permanently failed
    else Validation passes
        EE->>GM: Submit artifact for governance
        GM->>GM: Apply policies and standards
        opt Human approval required
            GM->>GM: Approval Gate Manager routes to human actor
            Note over GM: Human actor approves or rejects
        end
        GM->>KR: Persist approved artifact
        GM->>GM: Audit Logger records state change
        GM->>TM: Task Completed signal
        TM->>TM: Mark task Completed; unblock dependent tasks
    end
